{
  "predecessor": <full PCA_i>,
  "successor": {
    "ops": ["read:orders/*"],
    "executor": {
      "binding": "spiffe://example.com/svc/order-processor"
    },
    "constraints": {
      "temporal": { "exp": 1770000120 }
    }
  },
  "attestations": [
    {
      "type": "spiffe_svid",
      "svid": "<X.509 SVID for E_i>",
      "pop": "<PoP signature — see next breakdown>"
    }
  ]
}

The full PCA_i is included so the CAT can verify the
chain locally without database lookups. ops_{i+1} =
(read:orders/*) is a strict subset of ops_i — E_i has
VOLUNTARILY narrowed authority before calling a service
that only needs read access.

This is where principle of least privilege gets
enforced cryptographically rather than by convention.
